headline: Williams price target raised to $57 from $56 at CIBC
summary: CIBC analyst Robert Catellier raised the firm’s price target on Williams (WMB) to $57 from $56 and keeps a Neutral rating on the shares. The Williams Companies disclosed an agreement with a large investment-grade company to provide onsite natural gas and power generation infrastructure. While full details regarding the deal are limited, the firm views the agreement as a minor step-out project for the company, but one that is manageable and increases its price target Published first on TheFly – t

headline: These High-Yield Dividend Stocks Are Stomping on the Gas and Revving Up Their Growth Engines
summary: Higher-yielding dividend stocks tend to be slower-growing companies.  Pipeline companies have fit that description in recent years as their growth has slowed.  Natural gas pipeline giant Kinder Morgan (NYSE: KMI) has been running on fumes in recent years.
